# Interpreter for ___dumpenv1 - Dump .env/local/ variables with profile filtering
#
# The dumpenv function generates executable shell commands (setenv calls)
# for recreating .env/local/ variables, filtered by profile (prologue/epilogue).
#
# Type: Terminal function (produces commands for dump output)
# Default: cat (output to stdout for capture/piping)
#
# Profiles:
#   prologue - Safe minimal set (base interpreters + paths, no function-specific overrides)
#   epilogue - Complete set (all variables including function-specific interpreters)
#
# Usage:
#   vpn-switch dumpenv prologue  # Generate prologue setenv commands
#   vpn-switch dumpenv epilogue  # Generate epilogue setenv commands
#   vpn-switch dump              # Calls both (via ___dump0)
#
# Override examples:
#   VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_dumpenv=tee /tmp/env-dump.log  # Output and log
#   VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_dumpenv=cat  # Default (explicit)
#
# Note: This function is called by ___dump0 to generate prologue and epilogue sections.
# Profile separation prevents restore breakage (function-specific interpreters in
# prologue would prevent imports/adds/links from executing during restore).
#
# Phase 3.1.4: Dump/restore prologue/epilogue separation
